SIMPLE: inchoate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inchoate
<hw>In"cho*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inchoatus</ets>, better <ets>incohatus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>incohare</ets> to begin.]</ety> <def>Recently, or just, begun;
beginning; partially but not fully in existence or operation; existing
in its elements; incomplete.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>In"cho*ate*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neither a substance perfect, nor a substance
<qex>inchoate</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inchoate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inchoate
<hw>In"cho*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To begin.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dr. H. More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inchoation</ent>⟦br⟧
